cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use falsify in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "falsify: pre-registration + CI for AI/ML accuracy claims"
abstract: >
  A single-file Python CLI that pre-registers AI/ML accuracy claims with
  SHA-256 over canonical YAML. The metric, threshold, dataset hash, and
  seed are committed to a hashed manifest before the experiment runs;
  any silent edit afterwards causes the next run to exit 3 and refuse
  to produce a verdict. The honest amendment path is `lock --force`,
  which writes a new audit entry while preserving the previous hash.
